column1: Some small green particles in water column similar- but not worse than last week.

column2: 79 degrees partly cloudy with a light breeze.  More green noticed in the water column- though water is still quite clear overall.  There has been blue green algae in spots with little water movement.
82 degrees with partly cloudy skies and breezy.  Some of green growth has diminished due to big rains the past week.
79 degrees + clear. Continued lots of green in water column- w/ some bigger globules.  Beaches have re-opened. Surprising clarity.
78 degrees and mostly cloudy with light breeze.  Lots of green strand algae throughout water column.

80 degrees and humid with hazy/partly cloudy skies. 80 degrees and humid with hazy/partly cloudy skies.  Lots of green algae strands in water column though water color still brown overall.  Some surface green algae noted along shoreline in parts in previous days.
67 degrees- and mostly clear.  Much less green algae strands in the water column.
73 degrees- no cloud cover though hazy.
66 degrees with partly could skies and breezy.  No more green algae visible in the water column.
